post_text:
Good Morning Parents,

This is a reminder that tomorrow (Thursday) we will be serving meals for an entire school week at a time. We have just been allowed to serve meals to any and all children in our community under the age of 18. The children do not need to be present and they do not need to be enrolled in our schools. Please take advantage of this opportunity to get good nutritious meals for our kids in need. This is a bulk meal pick up day for any and all students or nonstudents under the age of 18 residing in our community.

These meals continue to be distributed at Keyes Elementary School in the bus loading and unloading zone. The pickup times are from 11:30 to 12:30. Children do not need to be present. This will continue each week on Thursdays.

Our participation rate is very low and we encourage our families to participate. These are meals for a full school week and include breakfast and lunch.

Sincerely,
Dr. Helio Brasil
Superintendent

The meals will be provided to any student age 18 and under. The student must be present when picking up the meal. The meal will include breakfast for the following day and lunch. Meals will continue to also be offered at both the Turlock and Ceres campuses sites we previously shared with you

post_text:
Good afternoon,
This is to inform staff, parents, and community that Keyes Union School District will be following the county and surrounding districts move to suspend school at the end of the day on Wednesday, March 18 - Possibly Friday, April 3, 2020.

We want to give parents an opportunity to secure and arrange for childcare.

This is a fluid situation and I will keep you all posted as more details become available.

We will be securing curriculum packets for students to take home on Wednesday. I will also work on trying to secure meals while school is out. More information will be coming on this as we work on the details.

I promise to keep you all posted as I hear and know more.

Thank you for your cooperation and support. We will all get through this. The safety and well-being of our students and staff is the number one priority.

Thank You,
Dr. Helio Brasil
Superintendent

Sincerely,

post_text:
Good Evening,
This is to update you on the status of a gas leak on the Spratling Campus. PG&E has been on site an have turned off the gas to the campus. This will not impact the electrical nor water system. School will resume tomorrow at the regular time. The Wildcat Parent Night will be re-scheduled for a later date. Thank you for your understanding and cooperation. PG&E were absolutely amazing in checking the entire campus and assuring us that the campus is safe for students and adults. Repairs will begin tomorrow and gas will not be turned on until all repairs are complete. We took this incident very seriously and we are committed to the safety of our students, staff and community.

Thank You,
Helio Brasil
Superintendent

post_text:
Good Afternoon,

We are cancelling the Middle School Wildcat Parent Night Activity tonight. We are doing so as a precaution and following the direction of PG&E as a result of a possible gas leak. The After School Program Students have been moved to the Middle School and High School Charter facility and they are safe.
This is not effecting any other school site. It is simply Spratling.

The Spratling Campus is being secured and we will wait for PG&E to give us the all clear. The event will be res-scheduled. Thank you for your understand and cooperation.

Sincerely,
Helio Brasil

Dear Keyes Union School District Families,
I want to wish each and every one of you a very Merry Christmas, Happy Holidays, and Happy New Year! Please enjoy the time with your friends and families and always remember to give back to those in need.
Thank you for supporting our children, teachers, and staff. Your commitment to the Keyes Union School District is paramount to the success of all students and we greatly appreciate each and every one of you.
Finally, please take a moment to reflect on those who are serving in our Country and that cannot be with their families and those who may be alone during this time. Remember that the spirit of the season is one of love, generosity, and forgiveness. ‚ÄúIt is time to look upon the world‚Äôs busy life and become more interested in people than in things. It is forgetting thy self and finding time for others‚Äù (T.S. Monson).
Many wishes for a safe and happy holiday.
Happy New Year!

Sincerely,
Dr. Helio Brasil
Superintendent

post_text:
After School Program Changes Beginning Monday, September 23, 2019

Good Morning,

Beginning Monday, September 23, 2019 the after school program at Keyes Elementary School will be making some changes to provide greater security for our students. Beginning Monday the front gate at Keyes Elementary will be kept closed after school. Students in the after school program will need to be picked up from the 7th street gate adjacent to the cafeteria. This is needed to make sure our students are safe and entry on to campus can be monitored. We will use the gate on 7th street for both entry and exit of after school program. We will also be conduction safety drills during the after school programs in the coming weeks. Our goal is student safety and well-being. Thank you for your cooperation and support on this.

Thank You,
Helio Brasil
Superintendent

This is needed to make sure our students are safe and entry on to campus can be monitored. We will use the gate on 7th street for both entry and exit of after school program. We will also be conduction safety drills during the after school programs in the coming weeks. Our goal is student safety and well-being. Thank you for your cooperation and support on this.

Thank You,
Helio Brasil
Superintendent
